result.description:
Release v1.0 of **plot2DO** has multiple improvements and additions to the previous version:
* it can analyze genomic data from multiple organisms (*Saccharomyces cerevisiae*, *Drosophila melanogaster*, *Caenorhabditis elegans*, *Mus musculus* and *Homo sapiens*), not just yeast;
* it can align user-provided lists of sites;
* it can plot alignments of dyads (V-plots), 5' ends, and 3' ends;
* it can produce simplified plots (without one-dimensional occupancy and length histogram panels) – very handy for creating multi-panel plots;
* it can produce "squeezed" plots – very useful for analyzing a small genomic region (e.g. +1 nucleosomes, tRNA genes, etc);
* it can use a fixed color scale – handy for comparing multiple samples;
* it has a detailed tutorial including multiple usage examples.

For more details, see the tutorial from the *README.md* file.

Enjoy!
